Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of statistical and machine learning algorithms for power generation forecasting, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of real data for validation also suggests that it could fall under the category of data-centric computing (cs.DC). Finally, the focus on forecasting at a macro-area level suggests that it could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
